  "prompt": "What's the definition of vote margin?",
  "response": "Vote margin refers to the difference in the number of votes received by candidates or options in an election or referendum. It indicates how much one candidate or option has outperformed another. The vote margin can be expressed as a simple numerical difference (e.g., Candidate A receives 1,200 votes while Candidate B receives 1,000 votes, resulting in a vote margin of 200 votes in favor of Candidate A) or as a percentage of the total votes. Vote margins are critical for determining the outcome of elections, as they can indicate the level of support for each candidate or option and influence potential recounts or challenges, especially in closely contested races.",
